    "causal_summary": "`memorycausalstats` reports a `relationCoverage` block whose `backfillJob.command` is `memoryhealth({ autoRepair: true, confirmed: true })` and whose `remediationHint` says \"Run … to backfill relation coverage; prioritize caused.\" A code review of the 2026-06-04 \"optimize causal graph\" request found this is a no-op: `lib/causal/relation-coverage.ts` is a pure reporter (no edge writes), and the autoRepair handler (`memory-crud-health.ts`) only does FTS rebuild + orphaned-edge/vector cleanup — it never balances relations",
